(1) Search
-----------
==> sets or returns the querystring part of a URL, including the question mark (?)

==> The querystring part is the part of the URL after the question mark (?). This is often used for parameter passing.


EX: Get Query Of [http://localhost:3000/?do=add]
-----

	window.location.search // "?do=add" 
	
	Or
	
	location.search // "?do=add" 
	
	
EX: Set Query Of [http://localhost:3000]
-----

	window.location.search = "?do=update" // http://localhost:3000/?do=update
	
	Or
	
	location.search = "?do=update" // http://localhost:3000/?do=update
